210
00:12:31,184 --> 00:12:33,120
No more.

211
00:12:33,186 --> 00:12:34,621
(Manami) Ah...｡

212
00:12:36,623 --> 00:12:39,059
>> Yeah! (Kuroiwa) Uh...

213
00:12:39,126 --> 00:12:41,061
Huh! >> Ah…｡

214
00:12:41,128 --> 00:12:42,562
(Kuroiwa) Don't worry about it.

215
00:12:42,629 --> 00:12:46,066
>> What? (Kuroiwa) I'm listening to you.

216
00:12:46,133 --> 00:12:49,069
Why are you treating people like this...?

217
00:12:49,136 --> 00:12:53,073
>> Huh? Don't you understand? (Kuroiwa) Huh?

218
00:12:53,140 --> 00:12:59,579
>> I think Detective Kuroiwa and I are the same.

219
00:12:59,646 --> 00:13:04,584
Because you like Manami, right?

220
00:13:04,651 --> 00:13:13,593
♪～

221
00:13:13,660 --> 00:13:16,596
(Kuroiwa) Then what?

222
00:13:16,663 --> 00:13:21,668
I would never do something like this.

223
00:13:23,670 --> 00:13:28,608
The moment you steal the person you love from someone you love →

224
00:13:28,675 --> 00:13:32,112
I don't like myself anymore.

225
00:13:32,179 --> 00:13:34,181
Don't you even understand that?

226
00:13:35,615 --> 00:13:39,052
Why was this the only option?

227
00:13:39,119 --> 00:13:43,623
I'm sure I could have done more...

228
00:13:45,125 --> 00:13:48,562
Even if you don't kill someone →

229
00:13:48,628 --> 00:13:54,067
You don't have to do something so sad like pretending to be a ghost.

230
00:13:54,134 --> 00:13:57,070
>> [Manami-san, I don't think you'll notice even if I die]

231
00:13:57,137 --> 00:13:59,072
(Kuroiwa) [Please don't say that! ]

232
00:13:59,139 --> 00:14:02,075
[As long as I'm alive... As long as I'm alive →

233
00:14:02,142 --> 00:14:05,645
