>> Please do your best.

249
00:15:02,135 --> 00:15:04,571
Mr. Kuroiwa.

250
00:15:04,638 --> 00:15:06,573
(Kuroiwa) Stand.

251
00:15:06,640 --> 00:15:09,142
(Sound of footsteps running towards you) (Iori) Manami!

252
00:15:11,144 --> 00:15:12,579
(Manami) I'm sorry for worrying you.

253
00:15:12,646 --> 00:15:15,582
(Yuriko) I wish I could come a little earlier.

254
00:15:15,649 --> 00:15:19,085
(Iori) Kiryu's car ran out of gas. It's really bad.

255
00:15:19,152 --> 00:15:21,087
(Manami) Were you there? >> That's right.

256
00:15:21,154 --> 00:15:24,591
But he suddenly disappeared and I forgot something.

257
00:15:24,658 --> 00:15:26,159
(Manami) Is she gone?

258
00:15:27,661 --> 00:15:30,163
(Kiyosumi) Huh… hah…｡

259
00:15:32,165 --> 00:15:35,035
Ha ha ha ha...

260
00:15:35,101 --> 00:15:38,538
(Kiryu) Kiyosumi-san, it's been a while.

261
00:15:38,605 --> 00:15:41,541
(Kiyosumi) Oh... what are you doing? At a place like this.

262
00:15:41,608 --> 00:15:43,543
(Kiryu) Hiking.

263
00:15:43,610 --> 00:15:45,545
What about Tanizaki?

264
00:15:45,612 --> 00:15:48,048
(Kiryu) I won't go hiking with my ex-wife.

265
00:15:48,114 --> 00:15:52,552
Tsk... you're fucking me, you're kidding me.

266
00:15:52,619 --> 00:15:54,621
You're kidding, aren't you?

267
00:16:02,128 --> 00:16:04,064
〔what happened? Suddenly]

268
00:16:04,130 --> 00:16:08,068
[That's a bad guess, even though you're a detective.]

269
00:16:08,134 --> 00:16:11,137
Police secretly stalk citizens.

270
00:16:17,043 --> 00:16:23,984
(Police car siren)

271
00:16:24,050 --> 00:16:25,485
(Manami) Thank you for your hard work.

272
00:16:25,552 --> 00:16:27,987
(Kuroiwa) Ah, thank you for your hard work.

273
00:16:28,054 --> 00:16:30,990
Um...uh...｡

274
00:16:31,057 --> 00:16:33,993
earlier….

275
00:16:34,060 --> 00:16:35,495
(Manami) Yes.

276
00:16:35,562 --> 00:16:37,998
(Kuroiwa) I understand that.

277
00:16:38,064 --> 00:16:43,003
That's not the case with Manami-san and the police.

278
00:16:43,069 --> 00:16:46,005
(Manami) Ah... yeah.

279
00:16:46,072 --> 00:16:49,509
(Kuroiwa) But... for example.

280
00:16:49,576 --> 00:16:52,946
If I quit the police force...

281
00:16:53,013 --> 00:16:55,949
(Manami) Ah~ Um...｡

282
00:16:56,015 --> 00:16:59,452
Let me say it properly.

283
00:16:59,519 --> 00:17:04,457
There is absolutely nothing between me and Kuroiwa-kun.

284
00:17:04,524 --> 00:17:07,527
It has nothing to do with the police.

285
00:17:10,029 --> 00:17:13,466
So don't quit even if you make a mistake.

286
00:17:13,533 --> 00:17:16,970
An excellent person like Kuroiwa-kun quits like this →

287
00:17:17,036 --> 00:17:18,972
too good to waste.

288
00:17:19,038 --> 00:17:22,475
(Kuroiwa) Huh... Thank you.

289
00:17:22,542 --> 00:17:25,979
(Manami) That's why I'll continue...

290
00:17:26,045 --> 00:17:29,549
(Kuroiwa) Thank you very much as a colleague.

291
00:17:31,050 --> 00:17:33,553
(Manami) Yeah, nice to meet you.

292
00:17:42,328 --> 00:17:44,264
(Manami) Yaho! (Kuroiwa) Thank you for your hard work.

293
00:17:44,330 --> 00:17:46,266
(Emoto) Usu.

294
00:17:46,332 --> 00:17:48,268
(Manami) I mean →

295
00:17:48,334 --> 00:17:51,271
It's rare for someone to survive after receiving that electric current.

296
00:17:51,337 --> 00:17:53,273
>> Why is it "Immortal Emoto"?

297
00:17:53,339 --> 00:17:56,709
(Kuroiwa) And you were also aware that there was a culprit in the warehouse, right?

298
00:17:56,776 --> 00:17:58,711
>> That's a coincidence.

299
00:17:58,778 --> 00:18:02,215
The painkillers I gave to EITO were lying next to the warehouse.

300
00:18:02,282 --> 00:18:04,217
(Manami) Painkillers? >> Yes.

301
00:18:04,284 --> 00:18:07,220
When I got into a fight with that guy and threw him away →

302
00:18:07,287 --> 00:18:09,789
Looks like he hit me in the back.

303
00:18:13,793 --> 00:18:16,729
But in the end, it didn't decrease at all.

304
00:18:16,796 --> 00:18:18,731
I guess I'll just have to lose weight and be patient.

305
00:18:18,798 --> 00:18:20,733
(Sound of door opening) (Wanibuchi: Loudly) Whoa!

306
00:18:20,800 --> 00:18:23,736
You're here to die.

307
00:18:23,803 --> 00:18:26,239
(Sakatani) 2.5-dimensional sympathy, lol.

308
00:18:26,306 --> 00:18:29,742
(Tokujii) Have you ever done this while suffering from a compound fracture?

309
00:18:29,809 --> 00:18:31,744
(Manami) Huh? >> Thrill is exciting.

310
00:18:31,811 --> 00:18:35,248
(Manami) It was really natural! (Kuroiwa) He was really good.

311
00:18:35,315 --> 00:18:38,751
>> I wanted to see Wanibuchi's great performance again.

312
00:18:38,818 --> 00:18:40,753
What if the environment is set up?

313
00:18:40,820 --> 00:18:43,256
(Kuroiwa) Ah, but everyone please be careful.

314
00:18:43,323 --> 00:18:45,758
The real Ai-chan hasn't been caught yet.

315
00:18:45,825 --> 00:18:48,261
(Grandpa Toku) Hmm, I can understand that.

316
00:18:48,328 --> 00:18:50,763
Why are you pouring water now?

317
00:18:50,830 --> 00:18:53,700
(Manami) I'll definitely catch you.

318
00:18:53,766 --> 00:18:56,202
>> Wow, that's cool.

319
00:18:56,269 --> 00:18:58,204
This is what it means to be popular! Learn from me.

320
00:18:58,271 --> 00:19:01,207
(Kuroiwa) Huh? No, I'm surprisingly popular.

321
00:19:01,274 --> 00:19:03,710
(Manami) So what are you going to do after you get discharged from the hospital?

322
00:19:03,776 --> 00:19:07,213
>> Well, first of all, I'm looking for a job.

323
00:19:07,280 --> 00:19:08,715
(Manami) I see.

324
00:19:08,781 --> 00:19:11,718
>>Also... it becomes weaker.

325
00:19:11,784 --> 00:19:13,219
(Manami) Huh?

326
00:19:13,286 --> 00:19:17,724
>> Ever since Musho came out, I've been trying to become stronger with the intention of dying.

327
00:19:17,790 --> 00:19:23,229
If I don't, I won't be able to start over with my life.

328
00:19:23,296 --> 00:19:27,734
But EITO and Erazaki lectured me.

329
00:19:27,800 --> 00:19:31,237
(Erizaki) [EITO-kun wants to drink, do you want to make up? ]

330
00:19:31,304 --> 00:19:33,306
[Huh? I didn't say that, but]

331
00:19:35,808 --> 00:19:39,746
[Ah! This life has reached its limit, seriously.]

332
00:19:39,812 --> 00:19:42,248
(Erasaki) [Well, surprisingly, I'm starting to like it.]

333
00:19:42,315 --> 00:19:44,751
[This life] [Why? ]

334
00:19:44,817 --> 00:19:46,753
[Isn't it pretty interesting? ]

335
00:19:46,819 --> 00:19:49,255
[It's like living with people you don't normally interact with.]

336
00:19:49,322 --> 00:19:52,258
[If we get used to each other and get nervous, we won't take care of each other.]

337
00:19:52,325 --> 00:19:55,762
[Wow!] [Oh? ]

338
00:19:57,263 --> 00:20:00,199
[You're just scared of yourself changing, right?]

339
00:20:00,266 --> 00:20:04,704
[Indeed, the truly strong are those who can give up their strength.]

340
00:20:04,771 --> 00:20:07,207
[It's the first time we've come to an agreement]

341
00:20:07,273 --> 00:20:09,208
[You're being spoiled.]

342
00:20:09,275 --> 00:20:12,278
[You only have one life to start over]

343
00:20:15,782 --> 00:20:18,718
[It can change as many times as you like.]

344
00:20:18,785 --> 00:20:21,721
[You don't have to start over each time]

345
00:20:21,788 --> 00:20:24,724
♪～

346
00:20:24,791 --> 00:20:28,227
[If that's the case, say so from the beginning]

347
00:20:28,294 --> 00:20:31,731
[It's mostly written in "EITO's Daily Mood Calendar."]

348
00:20:31,798 --> 00:20:33,733
[It's time to display it in your room.]

349
00:20:33,800 --> 00:20:36,803
[I'll look for it at a used bookstore] [Indeed...]

350
00:20:38,304 --> 00:20:41,240
[Looks like you don't have any money hahaha...]

351
00:20:41,307 --> 00:20:44,243
[What's so funny about you, dude?]

352
00:20:44,310 --> 00:20:46,746
(Erasaki) [What is that? 〕 (EITO) 〔4800 yen〕

353
00:20:46,813 --> 00:20:48,748
(Erasaki) [No, it's a rip-off! ]

354
00:20:48,815 --> 00:20:58,191
♪～

355
00:20:58,257 --> 00:21:02,195
Even though they are mostly pushy →

356
00:21:02,261 --> 00:21:05,198
So bossy.

357
00:21:05,265 --> 00:21:07,700
(Manami) It's because I like it.

358
00:21:07,767 --> 00:21:09,702
>> Huh?

359
00:21:09,769 --> 00:21:13,773
(Manami) I want the person I love to be in a good mood.

360
00:21:16,275 --> 00:21:19,212
I want you to live in a good mood.

361
00:21:19,278 --> 00:21:21,781
It's okay if I become weaker.

362
00:21:24,784 --> 00:21:27,720
>> It will become weaker...

363
00:21:27,787 --> 00:21:29,722
I feel like dying.

364
00:21:29,789 --> 00:21:32,225
(Manami) Don't force yourself.

365
00:21:32,291 --> 00:21:34,227
>> Yes.

366
00:21:34,294 --> 00:21:36,295
(Manami) Then let's go.

367
00:21:38,798 --> 00:21:40,800
Emo-san?

368
00:21:49,809 --> 00:21:51,244
(Manami) No!

369
00:21:51,310 --> 00:21:53,246
Not yet!

370
00:21:53,313 --> 00:21:55,181
>> Was that a bit too forceful?

371
00:21:55,248 --> 00:22:00,687
(Manami) No, it's okay! That... don't change that.

372
00:22:00,753 --> 00:22:03,690
Keep being forceful... Keep it.

373
00:22:03,756 --> 00:22:07,193
Keep going... haha.

374
00:22:07,260 --> 00:22:10,697
I will definitely catch the culprit.

375
00:22:10,763 --> 00:22:12,265
See you then!

376
00:22:13,766 --> 00:22:18,705
[Absolutely nothing with me, Kuroiwa-kun]

377
00:22:18,771 --> 00:22:22,208
[Regardless of the police]

378
00:22:22,275 --> 00:22:29,215
♪～

379
00:22:29,282 --> 00:22:30,717
(Kuroiwa) Haa, maiden.

380
00:22:30,783 --> 00:22:32,218
(Strong tapping sound)

381
00:22:32,285 --> 00:22:34,220
Are you okay? (Kuroiwa) Sorry.

382
00:22:34,287 --> 00:22:37,223
>> He turned himself in! Ai-chan.

383
00:22:37,290 --> 00:22:38,725
(Kuroiwa) Huh?

384
00:22:38,791 --> 00:22:47,734
♪～

385
00:22:47,800 --> 00:22:52,238
(Male) Yes, I call myself Ai-chan→

386
00:22:52,305 --> 00:22:57,744
Killing people who come close to Manami Tanizaki...

387
00:22:59,245 --> 00:23:01,247
I gave instructions.
